HEADWORD: Iridectomy
<hw>Ir`i*dec"to*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, <?/,
iris + <?/ cutting out; <?/ out + <grk>te`mnein</grk> to cut.]</ety>
<fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>The act or process of cutting out a portion of
the iris in order to form an artificial pupil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

